"n./v.(从灾难中)抢救，海上救助 【英】 n./v.(从灾难中)抢救 ，海上救助(save sth. from loss, fire, wreck, etc.) 【记】 salv(救)+age→抢救; 【同】 参考：salvable(可抢 救的) n. /v. (从灾难中)抢救(使其船员或其货物免于火灾或沉船) 【记】salv = save, age－抢救 【参】salvation(n 拯救) 【记】源自save；save 中间有个l，象个救生的绳子；sail save 航行中救援 【相关】savage 兇狠，salvage 是save中间有个l，象个救生的绳子，这是与savage的区别 salvage (n.)  1640s, ""payment for saving a ship from wreck or capture,"" from French salvage (15c.), from Old French salver ""to save"" (see save (v.)). The general sense of ""the saving of property from danger"" is attested from 1878. Meaning ""recycling of waste material"" is from 1918, from the British effort in World War I. salvage (v.)  1889, from salvage (n.). Related: Salvaged; salvaging."
